reason.er.compositeObjects

Class Expression<T,U>

  • java.lang.Object
    • reason.er.objects.Predicate<T,U>
      • reason.er.objects.Concept<T,U>
        • reason.er.compositeObjects.Expression<T,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - generic
    U - generic
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExpressionNode

    public class Expression<T,U>
extends Concept<T,U>
    The Expression is a handle for grasping a tree of ExpressionNodes. It has a root and booleans to track whether it is complete or normalized.
    Author:
    Aaron Eberhart
